rmk: Apart from the delightful song that these birds make, they have a variety of calls which include a warning call that sounds like a cat mewing. Wells (2007) describes it as “cheeair”, HBW (2019) as “pzeeeu” and Robson (2002) as “pzeeew”. Sonogram and waveforms (Post 1) show that the call is short at 0.5 second san repeated at 2-2.5 second intervals and repeated many times (noted up to 15 times).
